Process called "get_required_fields_for" that takes type_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns a List of AnnotationFieldDef for the required fields of the given
    Note: annotation type, or 0 if the annotation is freeform (no required fields).

    If type_id is AC.BLOCK_ANNOTATION_REASONING:
        Return build_reasoning_required_fields()
    End If
    If type_id is AC.BLOCK_ANNOTATION_IMPLEMENTATION:
        Return build_implementation_required_fields()
    End If
    If type_id is AC.BLOCK_ANNOTATION_UNCERTAINTY:
        Return build_uncertainty_required_fields()
    End If
    If type_id is AC.BLOCK_ANNOTATION_KNOWLEDGE_REFERENCE:
